node.text:
The @newyorkairshow had vapes, on vapes, on vapes! 💨 

Now we’re back in #newjersey with two chances and locations to see us! We’ll be doing a full demonstration at the @millvillearmyairfield in Millville, and a heritage flyover at the Naval Air Station Wildwood Aviation Museum, in Cape May County this weekend Sept. 4-5th.

node.text:
Thanks for the awesome airshow Atlantic City! 

The team is off this weekend, but we’ll be in New Windsor for the New York International Airshow Aug. 28-29th!

node.text: The team won’t forget our time with our Norther neighbors — thank you Canada! Now we’re back in the states, and heading to the airshow in Owensboro, Kentucky, this weekend Aug. 14-15th!

node.text: Senior Airman Lauren Ooghe is one of the team’s avionics specialists, and during the airshow last week last week in her home state of Pennsylvania she had the unique experience of showing her mother what she does for the team and the U.S. Air Force. Avionics specialists like Ooghe are crucial to ensuring aircraft like the F-22 Raptor are mission ready by maintaining all flight computers, integrated avionics, and a multitude of electrical systems and components.

node.text: This years HFTC was AMAZING! It was great to see @f35demoteam, @viperdemoteam, @a10demoteam, and @airforceheritageflight. Here’s a quick video from our time this last week #RaptorNation!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by F-22 Raptor Demo Team on September 06, 2021 tagging @cabogunderson. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text:
Thank you @millvillearmyairfield for the amazing show! 

It was perfect weather with fantastic people and we hope to come back to #newjersey again soon.

Special thanks to all the #wwii and Vietnam veterans who came out to see our show. It’s always a humbling experience to talk to those who paved the way for us today. 🇺🇸

node.text:
The @newyorkairshow had vapes, on vapes, on vapes! 💨 

Now we’re back in #newjersey with two chances and locations to see us! We’ll be doing a full demonstration at the @millvillearmyairfield in Millville, and a heritage flyover at the Naval Air Station Wildwood Aviation Museum, in Cape May County this weekend Sept. 4-5th.

node.text:
The Dedication Pass is the most meaningful maneuver of our demonstration. It's normally dedicated to all those who've paid the ultimate sacrifice for our country, but this week, we've dedicated it to the 13 service members who lost their lives in Kabul, Afghanistan, and their families. We are deeply saddened by the loss of our fellow brothers and sisters in arms, and these American heroes will not be forgotten. 

— Navy Hospitalman Maxton W. Soviak, 22, of Berlin Heights, Ohio
— Marine Corps Lance Cpl. David L. Espinoza, 20, of Rio Bravo, Texas
— Marine Corps Lance Cpl. Rylee J. McCollum, 20, of Jackson, Wyo.
— Marine Corps Lance Cpl. Kareem M. Nikoui, 20, of Norco, Calif.
— Marine Corps Cpl. Hunter Lopez, 22, of Indio, Calif.
— Army Staff Sgt. Ryan C. Knauss, 23, of Corryton, Tenn.
— Marine Corps Lance Cpl. Jared M. Schmitz, 20, of St. Charles, Mo.
— Marine Corps Cpl. Daegan W. Page, 23, of Omaha, Neb.
— Marine Corps Sgt. Nicole L. Gee, 23, of Sacramento, Calif.
— Marine Corps Staff Sgt. Darin T. Hoover, 31, of Salt Lake City
— Marine Corps Sgt. Johanny Rosariopichardo, 25, of Lawrence, Mass.
— Marine Corps Cpl. Humberto A. Sanchez, 22, of Logansport, Ind.
— Marine Corps Lance Cpl. Dylan R. Merola, 20, of Rancho Cucamonga, Calif.

node.text:
The weather nearly stole the show Sunday, but we were able to rage all weekend at the @newyorkairshow !Whenever we come to #newyork we know we’re going to have a great time with amazing people. 

Big thanks to the @nyspolice and @ocsheriff for all their help this weekend. 

And we couldn’t have done it without support from the #stewartairnationalguardbase 

Lastly, and certainly not least, a huge shout out to our maintenance team who put in the hard work that makes our shows possible. 🙌🏽

node.text:
“On behalf of the U.S. Air Force and the commander of Air Combat Command General Mark Kelly…” 

Anyone who has been to one of our shows has heard these words at the start of our demonstration. And during our practice this week the commander of @aircombatcommand himself, @genmarkkelly came out to watch with a special guest, Maj. Gen. Aluf Amikam Norkin, commander of the @israeliairforce

And if you’re in the area be sure to catch us at the @newyorkairshow this weekend!

node.text: Thanks for having us Oregon! We enjoyed the scenery and all the kind people we’ve met. We can’t wait to come back again and show more of what our Air Force can do! 🇺🇸
